<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870324-0121 </DOCNO><HL> Williams Cos. Unit's Program</HL><DD> 03/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WMB </IN><DATELINE> TULSA, Okla.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Williams Cos. said its telecommunications unit began a $22 million program that will more than double the capacity of its fiber-optic system.    The unit, which provides long-distance service primarily to business users, said it expects to have the new circuits between the Kansas City, Mo., metropolitan area and Chicago and between Kansas City and Los Angeles available in about five months.    Williams is an oil and natural gas transmission and telecommunications company. </TEXT></DOC>